Object.Field: Logical schema for temporary export file location

Specify the name of logical schema defining the location the temporary export file will be stored before uploading to Object Storage. This must be a File technology logical schema. Oracle directory will be created based on this location. The temporary file will be stored on a file system acessible by source database.
Name of Oracle directory created on Source
Specify the name of Oracle directory used by Datapump to store export file and logs on Source. Default : ODI_DIR Use only uppercase names.
Specifies which data to compress before writing to the dump file set.

You can specify one of the following compression options: ALL - enables compression for the entire export operation. The ALL option requires that the Oracle Advanced Compression option be enabled. DATA_ONLY - results in all data being written to the dump file in compressed format. The DATA_ONLY option requires that the Oracle Advanced Compression option be enabled. METADATA_ONLY - results in all metadata being written to the dump file in compressed format. This is the default. NONE - disables compression for the entire export operation.
Specifies the compression algorithm to be used when compressing dump file data.

You can specify one of the following compression algorithm options: BASIC 혰 Offers a good combination of compression ratios and speed; the algorithm used is the same as in previous versions of Oracle Data Pump. LOW 혰 Least impact on export throughput and suited for environments where CPU resources are the limiting factor. MEDIUM 혰 Recommended for most environments. This option, like the BASIC option, provides a good combination of compression ratios and speed, but it uses a different algorithm than BASIC. HIGH 혰 Best suited for situations in which dump files will be copied over slower networks where the limiting factor is network speed.
Set this property to False only if you have a single source with no transaformations or a simple filter.
Create view on source work schema(True/False)

Set this property to True if you want to create view on source Work Schema (see source Physical schema settings). Note that Work Schema user should have select privileges to all source tables participating in the view select statement for the view to be valid. If set to False the view will be created in the schema of the currently connected user (see source Data Server settings). Note that SYSTEM schema cannot be remapped, meaning that if we set to False we should not be connected as SYSTEM. Because of restrictions in both cases we provide this option.
GROUP_PARTITION_TABLE_DATA value for DATA_OPTIONS parameter is only available with Oracle 12.2 or above. Set this option to False for any previous Oracle versions.
Specifies the maximum number of processes of active execution operating on behalf of the export job.

Specifies the maximum number of processes of active execution operating on behalf of the export job. This execution set consists of a combination of worker processes and parallel I/O server processes. The master control process and worker processes acting as query coordinators in parallel query operations do not count toward this total. The value that you specify for integer should be less than, or equal to, the number of files in the dump file set. Because each active worker process or I/O server process writes exclusively to one file at a time, an insufficient number of files can have adverse effects. This parameter enables you to make trade-offs between resource consumption and elapsed time. Default : 1
Specifies the maximum size of each dump file.

Specifies the maximum size of each dump file. If the size is reached for any member of the dump file set, then that file is closed and an attempt is made to create a new file, if the file specification contains a substitution variable or if more dump files have been added to the job. Syntax : integer[B | KB | MB | GB | TB] The integer can be immediately followed (do not insert a space) by B, KB, MB, GB, or TB (indicating bytes, kilobytes, megabytes, gigabytes, and terabytes respectively). Bytes is the default. The actual size of the resulting file can be rounded down slightly to match the size of the internal blocks used in dump files. Restrictions : - The minimum size for a file is 10 times the default Data Pump block size, which is 4 kilobytes. - The maximum size for a file is 16 terabytes.
Default : if the option is not set, it is equivalent to the maximum size of 16 terabytes.
Provide Credential name to connect to Object Storage. Default is ODI.
If set to False ODI will reuse existing credentail.
Logical schema for temporary Object Store location
Specify the name of logical schema defining the location the temporary export file will be stored in Object Storage staging area. This must be a Object Storage technology logical schema.
Sets the maximum number of worker processes that can load in parallel.

The value that you specify for integer specifies the maximum number of processes of active execution operating on behalf of the import job. This execution set consists of a combination of worker processes and parallel I/O server processes. The master control process, idle workers, and worker processes acting as parallel execution coordinators in parallel I/O operations do not count toward this total. This parameter enables you to make trade-offs between resource consumption and elapsed time. Default : 1
Set this property to True if you want temporary objects to be automatically cleaned up.
Set this property to True if you want credential object to be automatically cleaned up at the end of the execution. Cleanup will only happen if CREATE_CREDENTIAL was set to True.

COMPONENT NAME: LKM Oracle to ADWC Datapump COMPONENT VERSION: 1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.2.1.4.0 or above
DESCRIPTION This LKM will load data from Oracle On-premises to Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud. It is using Oracle Datapump to unload data from source and load into ADWC. It has to be used in combination with Oracle or generic SQL IKM.
First source table is exported into local Datapump dump file. The export file is created in a local directory specified by TEMP_FILE_SCHEMA logical schema. Export file name is uniquely generated as odi_<ODI_session_id>_<mapping_node>.dmp. Export log name is odi_<ODI_session_id>_<mapping_node>_exp.log. The export file is then uploaded to object storage bucket specified by TEMP_OBJECT_STORAGE_SCHEMA logical schema. It is then imported from there to ADWC database into temporary staging table C$_<alias>. Import log name is odi_<ODI_session_id>_<mapping_node>_imp.log. Finally the mapping IKM is integrating the staging table into target. Transformations on target execution unit are supported.
Restrictions : 1. ODI agent has to run on the same host as the source database to be able to access dump/log files.
